messages.content: What is the latest version of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
The latest version of failfast-comfyui-extensions is 1.7.0, released on 2023-08-26.
What feature was added in version 1.7.0 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
In version 1.7.0, the feature to add hidden to global LinkRenderModes was added.
What was removed in version 1.6.1 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
In version 1.6.1, the links render mode was removed.
What bug was fixed in version 1.5.1 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
In version 1.5.1, a bug related to colors was fixed, where the default value of the color picker was set.
What feature was introduced in version 1.5.0 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
Version 1.5.0 introduced the feature to allow dot & microdot in reroute.
What feature was added in version 1.4.0 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
In version 1.4.0, the feature to allow copying images was added.
What feature was introduced in version 1.3.0 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
Version 1.3.0 introduced the feature to allow Reroute as dot.
What feature was added in version 1.2.0 of failfast-comfyui-extensions?
In version 1.2.0, the feature to allow showing the title on reroute was added.
What is the purpose of the Code of Conduct for the blibla-comfyui-extensions community?

The purpose of the Code of Conduct is to ensure that participation in the blibla-comfyui-extensions community is a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.
What are some examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment in the blibla-comfyui-extensions community?

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include demonstrating empathy and kindness toward other people, being respectful of differing opinions, viewpoints, and experiences, giving and gracefully accepting constructive feedback, accepting responsibility and apologizing to those affected by mistakes, and focusing on what is best for the overall community.
What are some examples of unacceptable behavior in the blibla-comfyui-extensions community?

Examples of unacceptable behavior include the use of sexualized language or imagery, sexual attention or advances, trolling, insulting or derogatory comments, personal or political attacks, public or private harassment, publishing others' private information without their explicit permission, and other conduct which could be considered inappropriate in a professional setting.
What are the responsibilities of community leaders in enforcing the Code of Conduct?

Community leaders are responsible for clarifying and enforcing standards of acceptable behavior, taking appropriate and fair corrective action in response to inappropriate behavior, and communicating reasons for moderation decisions when appropriate. They have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject contributions that are not aligned to the Code of Conduct.
Where does the Code of Conduct apply?

The Code of Conduct applies within all community spaces, and also applies when an individual is officially representing the community in public spaces, such as using an official e-mail address, posting via an official social media account, or acting as an appointed representative at an online or offline event.
How can instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior be reported?

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior can be reported to the community leaders responsible for enforcement at info@failfa.st. All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly, and all community leaders are obligated to respect the privacy and security of the reporter of any incident.
What are the consequences for violating the Code of Conduct?

The consequences for violating the Code of Conduct depend on the severity of the violation and can range from a private written warning to a permanent ban from any sort of public interaction within the community. The specific consequences are outlined in the Enforcement Guidelines section of the Code of Conduct.
What is the purpose of the Contributing Guide for ComfyUI Extensions?
The Contributing Guide for ComfyUI Extensions provides guidelines for individuals who wish to contribute to the project, ensuring they understand the process and expectations.
Where can contributors find the Code of Conduct for ComfyUI Extensions?
Contributors can find the Code of Conduct for ComfyUI Extensions in the CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md file.
What should contributors do before reporting a bug in ComfyUI Extensions?
Before reporting a bug, contributors should check the existing issues to ensure the bug has not already been reported.
How should contributors suggest enhancements for ComfyUI Extensions?
Contributors can suggest enhancements by opening an issue, labeling it as 'Feature Request', and detailing their suggestion, including why they believe it would be a good enhancement.
What is the process for submitting a pull request to ComfyUI Extensions?

To submit a pull request, contributors should fork the repository, clone it locally, create a new branch, make their changes, push the changes to their fork, and then create a pull request detailing the changes and reasons.
In what ways can contributors help improve the documentation for ComfyUI Extensions?
Contributors can help improve the documentation by clarifying language, correcting typos, or enhancing the design of the documentation.
What should contributors do if they have questions about contributing to ComfyUI Extensions?
If contributors have questions, they can open an issue labeled 'Question' or reach out to one of the project maintainers.
What is Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions?

Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions is a robust suite of enhancements designed to optimize the ComfyUI experience by providing features such as customizable render modes, dynamic node coloring, and versatile management tools.
How can users request a new feature for Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions?
Users can request a new feature by opening a Feature Request issue on the GitHub repository of failfast-comfyui-extensions.
What are the three methods available for installing Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions?

The three methods available for installing Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions are: loading via ComfyUI manager, cloning the repository directly into the extensions directory, and downloading the project manually.
What options are available in the settings of Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions?
The settings of Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions include options such as Force Snap to Grid, Force Box Shape, Render Shadows, Connections Width, Font Size, and Colored Nodes.
How does the 'Positive/Negative' coloring option in Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions work?

In the 'Positive/Negative' coloring option, nodes with titles containing 'negative' will be colored red, and nodes with titles containing 'positive' will be colored green, based on the node title in a case-insensitive manner.
What are the dynamic coloring modes available in Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions?
The dynamic coloring modes available in Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions are default, plain, by type, and rainbow.
How can users contribute to the development of Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions?
Users can contribute to the development of Blibla's ComfyUI Extensions by following the guidelines provided in the CONTRIBUTING.md file in the repository.
